---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Why Distilled CS exists, who built it, and how a vendor-neutral CS maturity framework helps practitioners cut through tool-vendor noise.">

  <div class="container about-page">

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-title">About Distilled CS</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">
        An open, vendor-neutral framework for Customer Success maturity.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="page-body">
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>What is Distilled CS?</h2>
        <p>
          Distilled CS is a community-driven framework that gives Customer Success teams a shared language for measuring maturity, setting benchmarks, and building repeatable processes. It is inspired by what the FinOps Foundation did for cloud cost management — providing an open standard where none existed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Why we built this</h2>
        <p>
          Every CS team reinvents the wheel — building health scores from scratch, guessing at benchmarks, and hoping their metrics are the right ones. Existing frameworks are paywalled, vendor-locked, or too generic to be useful. Distilled CS aims to change that by offering a practical, context-aware framework that adapts to your stage of growth, team size, and customer segment.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>The Strategy Loop: Assess → Execute → Transform</h2>
        <p>
          Distilled CS is built around a continuous improvement cycle — a repeatable system your CS team returns to as it grows.
        </p>
        <div class="loop-phases">
          <div class="loop-phase">
            <h3>Assess</h3>
            <p>Score your CS maturity across 8 domains. Understand your strengths, gaps, and current stage — from Crawl to Fly.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="loop-phase">
            <h3>Execute</h3>
            <p>Follow stage-specific strategy playbooks, track the right metrics, and work through your execution checklist.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="loop-phase">
            <h3>Transform</h3>
            <p>Measure your progress, compare against your previous assessment, and level up to the next maturity stage.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          The 4-stage maturity model — Crawl, Walk, Run, Fly — is the axis the strategy loop rotates around. Each time you complete the loop, your team moves closer to the next stage.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Open source & community</h2>
        <p>
          Distilled CS is licensed under <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>. No vendor lock-in, no paywall, no hidden agenda. Built by practitioners, for practitioners. Any adaptations must be shared under the same license.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Get started</h2>
        <p>
          Ready to find out where your CS team stands? <a href="/assess/">Take the free maturity assessment</a> — it takes about 5 minutes and gives you a personalized strategy starting point.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding-block: 3rem 5rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.125rem);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .page-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .content-section p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .content-section a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .content-section a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  .loop-phases {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .loop-phases {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .loop-phase {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }

  .loop-phase h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .loop-phase p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
